   <section id="tech" class="tab-pane fade"> 
    <div class="row space-t-5"> 
     <h1 class="strike"> <span>Technologies</span> </h1> 
    </div> 
    <div class="row space-t-6"> 
     <div class="col-lg-12"> 
      <p> The list below shows the technologies we use in our daily work. We are big advocates of <strong>open source technology</strong>, because of the <strong>stability</strong>, <strong>openness</strong> and <strong>customization</strong> possibilities of these libraries. The usage of an open source technology stack helps our customers <strong>to keep IT costs low</strong>, as no software license fees have to be paid. </p> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
    <div class="row cards space-t-8"> 
     <h3>Software and Web-Development Languages</h3> 
     <div class="row cards space-t-2"> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header python"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/python-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>Python is our weapon of choice for most use cases. It is easy to maintain, beautiful to read, has a great community around the world and is used by Google, Twitter, Pixar and many more.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header xcode"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/xcode-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>XCode is an integrated development environment (IDE) for developing software for OS X and iOS. It allows us to create native IPhone and IPad apps.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header javascript"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/javascript-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>JavaScript is a dynamic computer programming language. We use it to do create dynamic stuff at the front-end, and to create non-blocking server side applications using nodejs.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header angularjs"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/angularjs-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>AngularJS is an open-source JavaScript framework maintained by Google that allows us to build huge JS applications.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header html5"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/html5-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>HTML5 is a markup language for structuring and presenting content in the internet, and allows us to build apps that run everywhere. From PC to Smartphone to TV.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header css3"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/css3-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>CSS3 is a web-based markup language used to describe the look and feel of a website. It helps us to make our applications look appealing and beautiful. </p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
    <div class="row cards space-t-8"> 
     <h3>Frameworks</h3> 
     <div class="row cards space-t-2"> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header django"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/django-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>Django is the web framework for perfectionists with deadlines. It is a high-level Python web framework that encourages rapid development and clean, pragmatic design.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header phonegap"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/phonegap-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>PhoneGap allows us to create mobile applications using standard web technologies that run everywhere. From IPhone, to Android, to WindowsPhone.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header node"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/nodejs-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>nodejs is a software platform that is used to build scalable network applications. It allows us to build web applications that are incredibly fast.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
    <div class="row cards space-t-8"> 
     <h3>Databases</h3> 
     <div class="row cards space-t-2"> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header postgresql"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/postgresql-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>PostgreSQL is the worlds most advanced open source database. PostgreSQL is famous for its reliabilty and its stability.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header mongodb"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/mongodb-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>MongoDB is an open-source document database, and the leading NoSQL database. </p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header redis"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/redis-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>Redis is an open source, advanced key-value store. It is known for its performance as it stores data in memory, while having also build-in persistence.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header cassandra"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/cassandra-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>Cassandra database is the right choice when you need scalability and high availability without compromising performance.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
    <div class="row cards space-t-8"> 
     <h3>Threading, Messaging and Queues</h3> 
     <div class="row cards space-t-2"> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header celery"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/celery-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>Celery is an open source asynchronous task/job queue. It is focused on real-time operation, but supports scheduling as well.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header rabbitmq"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/rabbitmq-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>RabbitMQ is used for sending and receiving messages. Data delivery, non-blocking operations, push notifications or asynchronous processing are common tasks executed with RabbitMQ. </p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
    <div class="row cards space-t-8"> 
     <h3>System Administration and Source Code Management</h3> 
     <div class="row cards space-t-2"> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header linux"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/linux-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>Linux is the free operating system that powers thousands of webservers today. It is known for its stability, configurability and performance. We run our applications on Linux powered webservers.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header saltstack"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/saltstack-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>We provision our webservers using SaltStack. It helps us to maintain all the configuration stuff in one place and run our servers more secure and more stable.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-4"> 
       <div class="logo-card"> 
        <div class="logo-card-header github"> 
         <img src="/static/img/logos/jpg/github-logo.jpg" class="img-responsive"> 
        </div> 
        <div class="logo-card-text text-left"> 
         <p>git is a revision control and source code management software. It helps us to organize our source code and work in parallel. GitHub helps us to collaborate and facilitates the process of deployment.</p> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
   </section> 
